<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="587" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,726,969]" pageId="4" pageNumber="587">
The key includes some characters previously used to recognized species groups following 
<bibRefCitation author="Estevez, A. L. &amp; Polhemus, J. T." pageId="4" pageNumber="587" pagination="151 - 158" refId="ref5782" refString="Estevez, A. L. &amp; Polhemus, J. T. (2001) The small species of Belostoma (Hemiptera: Belostomatidae). I. Introduction, key to species groups and a revision of the denticolle group. Iheringia, Serie Zoologia, 91, 151 - 158. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / S 0073 - 47212001000200021" type="journal article" year="2001">Estévez &amp; Polhemus (2001)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Ribeiro, J. R. I." box="[280,447,762,788]" pageId="4" pageNumber="587" pagination="1 - 70" refId="ref6106" refString="Ribeiro, J. R. I. (2007) A review of the species of Belostoma Latreille, 1807 (Insecta, Heteroptera, Belostomatidae) from the four southeastern Brazilian states. Zootaxa, 1477 (1), 1 - 70. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 1497.1.1" type="journal article" year="2007">Ribeiro (2007)</bibRefCitation>
, in combination with new characters based mainly on the head, pronotum and hindwing, making it also possible to identify females. Nevertheless, for small-sized species groups, in many cases, it is impossible to recognize the species groups without male genitalic information. 
<taxonomicName authority="(Montandon, 1899)" baseAuthorityName="Montandon" baseAuthorityYear="1899" class="Insecta" family="Belostomatidae" genus="Belostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="587" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aurivillianum">
<emphasis box="[1000,1280,834,860]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="587">Belostoma aurivillianum</emphasis>
(Montandon, 1899)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Amyot &amp; Serville, 1843)" baseAuthorityName="Amyot &amp; Serville" baseAuthorityYear="1843" box="[274,674,870,896]" class="Insecta" family="Belostomatidae" genus="Belostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="587" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stollii">
<emphasis box="[274,371,870,896]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="587">B. stollii</emphasis>
(Amyot &amp; Serville, 1843)
</taxonomicName>
were previously treated in separate groups, but share some unique features, such as the carinas on the vertex, pronotum and posterior part of the scutellum, in addition to the vertex being straight below the ocular line. For this reason, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Montandon" baseAuthorityYear="1899" box="[715,898,942,968]" class="Insecta" family="Belostomatidae" genus="Belostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="587" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aurivillianum">
<emphasis box="[715,898,942,968]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="587">B. aurivillianum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is treated here as a member of the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Amyot &amp; Serville" baseAuthorityYear="1843" box="[1290,1354,942,968]" class="Insecta" family="Belostomatidae" genus="Belostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="587" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stollii">
<emphasis box="[1290,1354,942,968]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="587">stollii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
